# parse(_:)

**Instance Method**

Parses a value, using this strategy.

## Declaration

```swift
func parse(_ value: Self.ParseInput) throws -> Self.ParseOutput
```

## Parameters

- **value**: A value whose type matches the strategy’s [doc://com.apple.foundation/documentation/Foundation/ParseStrategy/ParseInput] type.

## Return Value

A parsed value of the type declared by [doc://com.apple.foundation/documentation/Foundation/ParseStrategy/ParseOutput].

## Discussion

This method throws an error if the parse strategy can’t parse `value`.
